## ğŸ“˜ Problem 2: Maximum Erasure Value (Max Sum of Unique Subarray)

### ğŸ“ Problem Description:
You're given an array of positive integers. You must find the maximum sum of a subarray with **only unique elements**.

### ğŸ’¡ Input:
- An integer array `nums` of length n.

### ğŸ¯ Output:
- A single integer â€” the maximum possible sum of a subarray with all unique elements.

### ğŸ§ª Example:
| Input          | Output |
|----------------|--------|
| nums = [4,2,4,5,6] | 17     |

Subarray `[2,4,5,6]` has unique elements and sum = 17.

---

### ğŸš€ Approaches:

| Approach               | Time Complexity | Space Complexity |
|------------------------|------------------|------------------|
| Brute Force            | O(nÂ²)            | O(1)             |
| Sliding Window + HashSet (Efficient âœ…) | O(n)              | O(n)             |

